5 Add Code
We are now ready to actually add code to our package! Go ahead and make a new R script in your “R” folder and name it “cv.R”. Once you have that file, click the collapsed menu below and copy/paste all of its contents into your empty “cv.R” file.


cv() Function - Version 1


cv &lt;- function(x = NULL, na_rm = TRUE){

  # Check input(s)
  if(is.null(x) || is.numeric(x) != TRUE)
    stop("'x' must be numeric")

  if(is.logical(na_rm) != TRUE){
    warning("'na_rm' must be a logical. Coercing to TRUE.")
    na_rm &lt;- TRUE 
  }

  # Calculate SD and mean
  sd_x &lt;- sd(x = x, na.rm = na_rm)
  avg_x &lt;- mean(x = x, na.rm = na_rm)

  # Calculate coefficient of variation
  coef_var &lt;- sd_x / avg_x

  # Return that 
  return(coef_var)
}
